node.text:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 
🔥FRIDAY FULL BODY HIIT🔥
Don’t forget to double tap & bookmark! ♥️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It’s OK if you don’t have a gym membership, it’s OK if you don’t have any equipment, it’s OK if you can’t find a babysitter, it’s OK if you’re a little unsure or have no clue as to what the hell you are doing in the first place.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Just get moving! The more you move your body, the more confident + comfortable you’ll get, and the more energy you’ll feel! By finding at least 30 minutes to get moving a day, you’re drastically going to make a difference in your health than being sedentary. Fight for your health. ♥️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
CIRCUIT:
1️⃣ Lunge Switch
2️⃣ Squat Jump Knee Tap
3️⃣ Traveling Lunge - Reverse Lunge - Squat Tip Toe 
4️⃣ Half Plank Oblique Kick
5️⃣ Standing Leg Extension
6️⃣ Lunge Switch
7️⃣ Squat Jump Knee Tap
8️⃣ Traveling Side - Side Squat
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
METHOD: 
Perform each exercise for 30-60 seconds. Complete 3 rounds total. 5 minute rest between each round. Finish with a light cool down and stretch.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
OUTFIT:
@gymshark @gymsharkwomen
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#brittnebabe #brittnejackson
@brittnebabe @brittnejackson
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
I was born in Queens, NY, but was raised in Jerseyyy! The town with the best club music-hands down #jerseygirl #jerseyclub. This is what I grew up on. Shout out to my boyfriend for the track 😅👌
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Even with life changing circumstances, I manage to continue doing what I love. And that’s taking care of both my mind and body the best way I know how. I love educating, I love encouraging, and I love sharing my journey with you all. I’m working on being more vulnerable and showing you guys all of me during this new journey of my life. You all keep me going. Hope this bring a smile to your face 😆💕
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#brittnebabe @brittnebabe

node.text: A good woman will stay by your side no matter how much you lie, cheat, or steal. That woman is your mother, NOT us. 🤣 #HappySaturday 😏

[swipe + save for later]
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
BOOKMARK THIS VIDEO + #DOUBLETAP if you'd like to get rid of those love handles, improve your stability, strengthen your core, build your booty, tone your back, arms, and legs allll at the same time!!! Make sure you keep that core tight during each movement. You have to feel the results happening. THINK with your core. 😖💪
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
(PS: We can’t spot reduce fat. It’s impossible, however there’s a combination of nutrition and exercise that will lead you into the right direction.)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
CIRCUIT: (3 or 5 rounds total)
1️⃣ Leg Lift
(3 rounds x 20 reps each leg)
2️⃣ Leg Drop
(3 rounds x 20 reps)
3️⃣ Don’t Drop, Lower Leg Rock
(3 rounds x 45 seconds or til failure)
4️⃣ Around the World
(3 rounds x 15 reps)
5️⃣ In & Out Crunch
(3 rounds x 15 reps)
*Rest 2-3 minutes between rounds! 🥵

node.text:
ABS + LEAN LEGS 😍😍😍
Don’t forget to double tap & bookmark! ♥️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If your goal is to obtain a tight, toned tummy, leaner legs, there is something you need to keep in mind. One, you CANNOT SPOT REDUCE FAT. The human body is incredibly unique and will distribute that in its own way. Nutrition (100%) + Exercise (100%) go hand in hand. Now, the good news is that there are some training styles that can HELP you obtain the appearance you are looking for. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
EXERCISES:
⭐️ #1 ( 3 x 10 per leg ) 
⭐️ #2 ( 3 x 15 )⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️ #3 ( 3 x 12 per leg )
⭐️ #4 ( 3 x 15 )
⭐️ #5 ( 3 x 15 each side: left, middle, right)
⭐️ #6 ( 3 x 60 seconds )
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
METHOD: 
Complete 3 rounds total. 5 minute rest between each round. Finish with a light cool down and stretch.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
OUTFIT:
@gymshark @gymsharkwomen
(Click link in bio to shop my look 😍)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#brittnebabe @brittnebabe

node.text:
A year ago, I honestly didn’t see myself still here. Losing your mom, your world, is tougher than the word itself. It’s something you can’t explain, but more so experience. If you haven’t lost a parent, you’ll never understand... but I’m still here and I’m soooo proud of me. I truly am. 🤎✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If there’s anyone like me out there who is going through what I’m going through, you can do it. The shit is wild and it will have you going through every emotion, but you can get through it. It’s a process and let me tell you - you’re a lot stronger for keeping on and healing from it. God doesn’t give the hardest battles to his toughest soldiers, he creates the toughest soldiers out of life’s hardest battles. I need you to remember that. ✨🧡🧡🧡✨

Listen up babes - I encourage everyone to complete a mini workout with SOME sort of movement EVEN on your rest days.  Low impact is fine, but add a little high impact in there... It’s like the cherry on top of a yummy, bomba$$ sundae. 🍨 You can use ankle weights no lighter than 5 lbs (totally optional).
